In this regard, music readers (especially the most rudimentary) are much more performing.
In the case of cheap mobiles, expect that they will only play music for a few hours.
If, in addition, you get to call from time to time, find, to be sure, a second charge for the job - this being even valid for the more expensive devices.
The problem will not arise for MP3 players who are capable of continuous operation of at least 9 hours, including the least performing ones.
