Common transport (MHD) will introduce chips into their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be included in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragoise Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will board the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
Currently, it is accessible for about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day coupon or 90-day coupon (which will be valid from 1 January 2009) and have it recorded on their chips card in the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located in the Metro Stations Museum, MČetek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday onwards, there is also the possibility to purchase coupons via the Internet on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they so far have to tread impatience in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon online and will record it on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is at the disposal of passengers a window with trained staff, which will help those interested with the purchase via the Internet and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Alongside libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recall the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the Roztyly Metro Stations, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be ninety," Opatrný added.
A machine will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will run from tomorrow are easy to use.
Simply enter the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
