The 15 million euros provided by the Municipality of Madrid constitute a "unique opportunity" for Garci to reproduce with the appropriate decorations and clothing the atmosphere of "a Spain that has been deceived as a leader in the fight, since the struggle for independence has led the people to rebellions under the reign of Ferdinand VII", he said.
But the filmmaker regrets that he did not get funding like for the films "Capitaine Alastriste" or "The Ghosts of Goya" - more than double the one obtained for "Sangre de mayo" - because he could not shoot a few scenes written in a script signed by Horacio Valcárcel, with whom he collaborated during almost all his career.
The filmmaker of "Back to Start" influenced his usual way of working, on the stage of the actors, with whom he is used to repeat before starting the shooting and to whom he does not do casting, since it seems to him "humiliating" and considers that "the role of the filmmaker is to go to the theatre and the cinema to keep himself informed".
Many actors in "Sangre de mayo" repeat in front of the camera, such as Miguel Rellán, Carlos Larrañaga or Fernando Guillén Cuervo.
Four times candidate for Oscar (he won one), Garci considers that the three films that represent Spain this year at the Academy of Hollywood, "Sangre de mayo", "Seven tables of French billiard" and finally the winner, "The blind sunflowers", are not representative of the young Spanish cinema, "which would deserve to be better known," he said.
