The superneck to walk on the walls.
Conquer the laws of gravity with a super glue and, in the future, walk on walls like Spiderman.
This is the goal of various American research centres, and today, a team of four institutes has almost succeeded.
With an adhesive measuring only 2.5 square centimeters, the researchers managed to maintain a body of 100 kilograms on a vertical wall.
The ETUDE- The American journal Science has published the findings of some researchers from the University of Dayton, Akron, the Georgia Institute of Technology and the Air Force Research Laboratory.
The material, invented by the team of researchers, is an evolution of those we know who use a specific carbon structure, called nano carbon tubes.
"The glue principle can be imagined as a series of tubes arranged like a stack of spaghetti." Explains Zhong Lin Wang from the Georgia Institute of Technology of Atlanta.
Scientists have been inspired by geckos' legs, covered with microscopic hairs that make it possible to ensure the animal, a perfect adherent.
Tests on various materials, such as glass, Téflon, and glass paper, have demonstrated that the new adhesive is ten times more powerful than the legs of these reptiles, and at the same time, that "it easily separates itself from the wall" explains Liming Dai, a researcher at the University of Dayton Engineering.
MARKET ON WOMEN? –"This material could be used as a temporary adhesive" adds Limiting Dai.
Could it be to walk on walls like Spiderman? Maybe so, but researchers think of a much less fascinating use such as the connection between electronic devices, since the nano carbon tubes are conductors of heat and electric current.
Other applications could concern aerospace engineering.
For now, no superheroes.
THE OTHER RESEARCH- The University of Berkeley, California, is also looking for a new adhesive.
In an article by the American Chemical Society, Californian researchers presented an adhesive made up of microfibres such as hair, which self cleanses dust during movement on a surface to ensure a perfect and constant adherence.
