At 26 years old, Kohl is the fourth positive cyclist in Cera, the third generation Epo, after the Italian Riccardo Ricco and Leonardo Piepoli, and the German Stefan Schumacher, also from Gerolsteiner.
Blood tests on Kohl specimens are part of those performed in recent weeks by the laboratories of Lausanne and Chatenay-Malabry.
If the counter-analysis confirms the positivity in Cera, the Austrian will lose its third place in the Tour and will have to hope for two years of elimination.
The news of Kohl's positivity at the third generation Epo was confirmed by the head of the French anti-doping agency, Pierre Bordry, who informed the Associated Press, that he had notified the positivity to the Austrian authorities.
The 26-year-old Austrian placed himself on the podium behind the Spanish Carlos Sastre and the American Cadel Evans, thus sharpening the peas jersey of the best climber.
